{"id": "19156", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki?curid=19156", "title": "Foreign relations of the Marshall Islands", "text": "Foreign relations of the Marshall Islands\n\nThe Republic of the Marshall Islands has established bilateral diplomatic relations with about 105 states. Regional cooperation, through membership in various regional and international organizations, is a key element in its foreign policy.\n\nThe Marshall Islands became a member of the United Nations on September 17, 1991. The Marshall Islands maintains embassies in the United States, Fiji, South Korea, Japan, and the Republic of China (Taiwan). They also maintain a consulate in Honolulu, Hawaii, USA and a consulate in Springdale, Arkansas, USA.\n\nIn May 2005, Chen Shui-bian, President of the Republic of China (Taiwan), became the first foreign head of state to make an official visit to the Marshall Islands.\n\nList of countries with diplomatic relations with the Marshall Islands:\nBULLET::::1. – 21 October 1986\nBULLET::::2. – 26 February 1987\nBULLET::::3. – 8 July 1987\nBULLET::::4. – 16 September 1987\nBULLET::::5. – 22 January 1988\nBULLET::::6. – 4 June 1988\nBULLET::::7. – 17 June 1988\nBULLET::::8. – 15 September 1988\nBULLET::::9. – 21 September 1988\nBULLET::::10. – 9 December 1988\nBULLET::::11. – 25 January 1990\nBULLET::::12. – 23 May 1990\nBULLET::::13. – 1 August 1990\nBULLET::::14. – 14 September 1990\nBULLET::::15. – 22 October 1990\nBULLET::::16. – 22 February 1991\nBULLET::::17. – 16 March 1991\nBULLET::::18. – 23 September 1991\nBULLET::::19. – 14 November 1991\nBULLET::::20. – 17 November 1991\nBULLET::::21. – 16 December 1991\nBULLET::::22. – 17 December 1991\nBULLET::::23. – 17 December 1991\nBULLET::::24. – 2 February 1992\nBULLET::::25. – 12 February 1992\nBULLET::::26. – 14 February 1992\nBULLET::::27. – 2 May 1992\nBULLET::::28. – 1 June 1992\nBULLET::::29. – 15 June 1992\nBULLET::::30. – 5 August 1992\nBULLET::::31. – 6 August 1992\nBULLET::::32. – 28 August 1992\