 (Korean shamanism), the native religion of Korea\nBULLET::::- Mu (shaman), a Korean priest\n\nBULLET::::- Mu phage, a bacteriophage of the family Myoviridae of double-stranded DNA non-enveloped contractile tail bacterial viruses\nBULLET::::- Centimorgan, or \"map unit\", a unit of recombinant frequency in genetics\nBULLET::::- Monitor unit (MU), a measure of absorbed dose from a linear accelerator in radiation therapy = 0.001 Gray\n\nBULLET::::- Chemical potential, a form of potential energy that can be absorbed or released during a chemical reaction\nBULLET::::- Bridging ligand, an atom that connects two or more metal centers in a complex (molecule)\n\nBULLET::::- MU puzzle, a puzzle in the book \"Gödel, Escher, Bach\"\nBULLET::::- Möbius function, a multiplicative function in number theory and combinatorics\nBULLET::::- Degree of membership in a fuzzy set\nBULLET::::- The standard measure function name in measure theory\nBULLET::::- Complex cobordism, an extraordinary cohomology theory\n\nBULLET::::- Micro-, SI (metric) prefix denoting a factor of 10 (one millionth)\nBULLET::::- Micrometre (deprecated as a single-character symbol)\nBULLET::::- Million units of energy, a term used in India for a gigawatt-hour, see kilowatt-hour#Other energy-related units\nBULLET::::- Mu (unit), a Chinese area also spelled \"mou\", approximately 0.066 hectares.\n\nBULLET::::- Coefficient of friction, used to approximate the force of friction\nBULLET::::- Deformation (mechanics), as the \"unit\" of strain\nBULLET::::- Electron mobility, relating the drift of electrons to the applied electric field across a material\nBULLET::::- Permeability (electromagnetism) coefficient, degree of magnetization of a material\nBULLET::::- Muon, an elementary particle\nBULLET::::- Standard gravitational parameter of a celestial body\nBULLET::::- Reduced mass, the \"effective\" inertial mass appearing in the two-body problem\nBULLET::::- Magnetic dipole moment, a measure of the strength of a system's 